<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--ShellExplosion     09-06 0186</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Shell Explosion,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Explosion, Major Fire at Shell Oil Refinery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MARTINEZ, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men were badly burned in an explosion
at the Shell Oil refinery that shot flames and smoke hundreds of
feet in the air and shook homes seven miles away.
   The first blast, shortly before 7 p.m. Tuesday, was followed by
more than a dozen smaller ones during the next 2{ hours, said Jane
Tocher, an engineering assistant at Shell. Officials said they
planned to let the fire burn itself out. There was no damage
estimate.
   Two Shell employees were seriously burned and taken to a San
Pablo hospital, where they were listed in stable condition in the
burn unit. Both had second-degree burns on 25 percent of their
bodies, mainly on their back and arms, a hospital spokesman said.
   Some 150 industry firefighters brought the blaze under control
about 9 p.m, said Shell spokesman Igor Skaredoff. The cause of the
explosion and fire were unknown.
   Nearby residential neighborhoods were not evacuated, but the sky
over Martinez was thick with black smoke that billowed high into the
sky over the plant.
</TEXT>
