<HEAD>Immigration Agent Slain, Another Wounded</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES throughout with police saying agents were investigating
and alien-smuggling operation, fourth suspected arrested. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRESNO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An undercover federal agent was shot to
death and another was wounded today while investigating an alien
smuggling operation, police said.
   Officers sealed off a neighborhood near the shooting scene in the
parking lot of a convenience store and arrested four suspects, one
by one, by 7 a.m., about 5{ hours after the shootings, police said.
   The agents were members of an Immigration and Naturalization
Service smuggling unit and had arranged to meet with the suspects in
the parking lot, said police Sgt. Rene Martin.
   ``As the agents approached and attempted to make contact, the
suspects fired at the agents,'' Martin said. ``Two backup agents
came onto the scene and exchanged fire. Some of the suspects got
back into the vehicle, and the vehicle drove away.''
   The car was found abandoned a few blocks away.
   Arrested were three men and a woman, Martin said.
   One agent was pronounced dead at Valley Medical Center, and the
other was taken into surgery, police said.
   A Highway Patrol helicopter with a searchlight helped look for
the suspects in the dark.
