<HEAD>Boat Capsizes off Indonesia; 28 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger boat with 175 people on
board sank in rough seas off eastern Java and at least 28 people
drowned, police said Wednesday.
   At least 101 people were missing after the boat sank in the
Madura Straits on Friday, said a police official in the provincial
city of Surabaya. The official, who spoke on condition of anonymity,
said the boat capsized after it was hit by huge waves.
   Local fishermen rescued 46 people, he said.
   The official said police received word of the accident only on
Monday and said naval ships and helicopters were still searching for
survivors.
