<HEAD>Six Killed, Almost 3,000 People Lose Homes in Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire in a squatters' settlement
destroyed more than 550 homes, and six people trying to flee the
flames in a boat drowned when the boat sank, police said Wednesday.
   The fire broke out Tuesday night in a settlement built over the
sea near Tawau, 730 miles east of Kuala Lumpur.
   Tawau Police Chief Chester Chong said 2,930 people were left
homeless and that 558 of the settlements' 1,818 houses were
destroyed. He said the casualty toll was expected to rise.
   Chong told the national news agency Bernama that the dead were a
50-year-old woman and five children whose boat sank as they fled the
fire.
   The cause of the fire was not known.
