<HEAD>US Asks Salvadoran Rebels To End Attacks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The State Department said Wednesday terrorist
attacks by leftist rebels in El Salvador must cease if proposed
peace talks are to have a chance for success.
   Spokeswoman Margaret Tutwiler made the statement after the FMLN
rebel movement accepted an offer by Salvadoran President Alfredo
Cristiani to hold discussions aimed at ending the country's 10-year
