<HEAD>Baseball Commissioner A. Bartlett Giamatti Laid to Rest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A. Bartlett Giamatti, major league
baseball commissioner and former Yale University president, was
buried today.
   At least 50 relatives and friends attended Giamatti's graveside
service at the Grove Street Cemetery, the traditional burial site
for Yale's presidents.
   Giamatti died Friday after suffering a heart attack at his summer
home on Martha's Vineyard in Massachusetts. He was 51.
   Among those at the cemetery were Yale President Benno C. Schmidt
