<HEAD>Chinese Trade Officials To Visit US</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A delegation of Chinese trade officials will
visit Washington to discuss with American officials China's
longstanding interest in joining the General Agreement on Trade and
Tariffs (GATT), the State Department said Wednesday.
   The United States has maintained an arms-length relationship with
China since the crackdown on pro-democracy demonstrators in June but
State Department spokeswoman Margaret Tutwiler said the upcoming
meeting was not inconsistent with that policy.
   No negotiations will be carried out during the consultations, she
said.
   The Chinese officials asked to visit the United States as part of
a lnger trip that would take them to Europe to discuss similar
issues with the European Community, she said. No date for the
meeting has been set.
   GATT is a 96-member grouping that seeks to regulate world trade.
