<HEAD>Portuguese Police Bust Drug Ring</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LISBON, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police broke up an international
narcotics ring that imported drugs in cans labeled as fruit and
tripe, and 10 people were arrested, news reports said Wednesday.
   Authorities also seized 440 pounds of cocaine, the reports said.
That amount of drugs would have a street value of about $50 million
in Portugal.
   Police arrested five Spaniards, three Portuguese, one Colombian,
and a Cuban-born American, according to the Portuguese news agency
Lusa. It did not identify them.
   It said they were suspected of importing drugs by ship from
Colombia and Equador, Lusa said.
   No police spokesman was available to comment, and the reports did
not say when or where the arrests and seizures were made.
   The drugs marked as fruit and tripe were destined for other
European countries, Lusa said.
   Police also seized six cars and $78,000, Lusa said.
