<HEAD>Swiss Extradite Lebanese Businessman Tied To German Scandal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERN, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Lebanese businessman was extradited
Wednesday to West Germany to face charges of fraud in an alleged oil
trading scandal, the Swiss justice ministry said.
   West German authorities accuse Khalil J. Ghattas of leading an
illegal scheme that cost Kloeckner and Co. oil trading house some
$303 million. Swiss police arrested him in March.
   Ghattas, 58, controls the Gatoil chain of gasoline stations in
Switzerland, which recently ran into financial trouble after he
built them up in the 1970s.
   He is charged with inciting a former chief dealer at Kloeckner
into massive speculation on international oil markets. The company,
based in Duisburg, West Germany, was taken over by Deutsche Bank
after running up huge losses with the alleged dealings.
