<FIRST>r f BC-GrandMet-Haagen-Dazs     09-06 0235</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Grand Met-Haagen-Dazs,0243</SECOND>
<HEAD>Grand Met Names Sorensen to Head Haagen-Dazs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Grand Metropolitan PLC said Wednesday it has
named a former executive with Pepsi-Cola International to be
president and chief executive at its Haagen-Dazs subsidiary.
   Ove Sorensen will direct all worldwide operations of Haagen-Dazs,
a premium ice cream brand, including Haagen-Dazs U.S.A., with annual
sales of approximately $250 million, and Haagen-Dazs International,
with annual sales of approximately $80 million.
   Sorensen, 47, who assumes his new duties immediately, was senior
vice president, marketing and sales, at Pepsi-Cola International, a
division of Pepsico. Before joining Pepsico, he held executive
positions with Mars Inc., Cavenham Ltd., W.R. Grace and Ted Bates
Advertising.
   ``Ove's extensive experience in the U.S. food industry, with
specific expertise in global sales and marketing, makes him an ideal
candidate to lead Haagen-Dazs into the 1990's,'' said Ian Martin,
chairman and chief executive of Grand Met's food sector and chief
executive of U.S. operations for the company.
   Martin said he and Sorensen will work together ``to maintain and
strengthen Haagen-Dazs' position as the leading premium ice cream
brand in the U.S., and to expand the Haagen-Dazs name in major
international markets.''
   Sorensen will be based at the headquarters office of Haagen-Dazs
in Teaneck, N.J.
   Grand Met, a London-based concern which last year acquired the
Minneapolis-based Pillsbury Co., is a leading international food,
drinks and retailing company with annual sales of $17 billion.
</TEXT>
