<SECOND>PM-Wall Street Closing,0144</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices declined broadly today in an
atmosphere of uncertainty about the outlook for Federal Reserve
policy and interest rates.
   Analysts said a belief was spreading among investors that the
Federal Reserve was unlikely to relax its credit policy further any
time soon, given a stronger-than-expected economy.
   ``At a minimum, the Fed is not going to provide the fuel to drive
the market further,'' said Hugh Johnson at First Albany Corp. in
Albany, N.Y.
   Johnson also said portfolio managers at investing institutions
seemed to be in a wary mood.
   ``Institutional money managers have had an exceptionally good
year, and they're all trying to figure out how to protect their
gains. Most of them don't have many alternatives other than to sell
stocks,'' he observed.
</TEXT>
