<FIRST>r f BC-BankSouthCutbacks     09-06 0175</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Bank South Cutbacks,0181</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bank South Corp. Plans 300-Job Reduction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bank South Corp. said Wednesday that a program to
boost its income by $15 million annually will include reducing the
company's work force by 10 percent, or about 300 jobs.
   ``We will reorganize certain areas, spread out layers of
management, eliminate duplications and, in general, cut costs,''
said President and Chief Executive Officer Robert P. Guyton. ``At
the same time, we are fully protecting our commitment to quality
service.''
   In a statement, Guyton said the reduction is in anticipation of a
slower economy and a more competitive banking industry in the 1990s.
Atlanta-based Bank South is a $5 billion multibank holding company
with 136 banking offices in Georgia and Pensacola, Fla.
   The bank said the restructuring should cut annual expenses by 8
percent to 10 percent, or about $15 million.
   The company said the job reductions would be phased in, with many
of them coming through attrition. Other affected employees, it said,
will receive help finding other employment and severance packages.
</TEXT>
