<FIRST>r f BC-DietCoke-Batman     09-06 0180</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Diet Coke-Batman,0187</SECOND>
<HEAD>Diet Coke To Help Launch ``Batman'' Video</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Diet Coke will join forces with ``Batman'' this
fall to help Warner Home Video launch the movie's videocassette
sales.
   A multimillion-dollar promotional campaign to begin in November
will include a 30-second commercial for Diet Coke that features
Alfred the Butler, the Batmobile and the Caped Crusader. At the end
of the commercial a tagline will announce the availability of the
videocassette.
   Filmed during production of the ``Batman'' movie, the commercial
stars Tony Award-winner Michael Gough as Alfred.
   The shot features Batman racing to ``Gotham Corner Store'' to
stock up on Diet Coke while Alfred phones ahead to warn the store
manager of his arrival, saying, ``Just look for a black car ...
rather difficult to miss ... and by the way, the gentleman is
usually in quite a rush.''
   The Gotham Corner Store commercial also appears in the
videocassette, which will be available Nov. 15.
   ``Batman'' is the all-time No. 4 film in terms of earned revenue
and the most successful movie in Warner Bros. history.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
